Synopsis:
In The International, Interpol Agent Louis Salinger 
and Manhattan Assistant District Attorney Eleanor 
Whitman are determined to bring to justice one of 
the world's most powerful banks. Uncovering illegal 
activities including money laundering, arms trading, and 
the destabilization of governments, Salinger and Whitman's 
investigation takes them from Berlin to Milan to New York 
and to Istanbul. Finding themselves in a high-stakes chase 
across the globe, their relentless tenacity puts their own 
lives at risk as the bank will stop at 
nothing - even murder - to continue financing terror and war.
